IMO these Marvel Shows on Disney+ never quite stick the landing in the last episode, but this one was probably the closest. Ends on a satisfying enough level, and surely they aren’t done with the character. Either a Season 2 or other crossovers are coming.

There’s a twist partway through that’s obviously trying to be the big mind blowing moment that makes you recontextualize everything, I was kinda bemused by it. Something I’ve seen in plenty of other stories. But then they use it for some legit good character work, which is great.

The action scenes are pretty meh, partly because it’s never really established what Moon Knight’s powers are, but they get the job done. What’s more fun are chase scenes and the like where the hero is fading in and out of varying levels of consciousness. Some clever stuff.

Interesting discussions being had over the change of Marc Spector (who was an Orthodox Jew) into a more modernized reformist Jew. I saw that bother some people. Didn’t bother me but I don’t really know anything about it, just wanted to mention it, it’s worth thinking about.

This first season is very light on the Marvel tie-ins, which I think was a smart move. I found myself more willing to wait for each episode than pre-established stuff like Loki, but ultimately it’s better that MK got to tell its own story.
